- #strong[Dynamism and Diversity];: We particularly emphasize that a WSI is not a single, monolithic entity. Instead, it can dynamically form, adjust its size and composition according to current cognitive demands, and even dissipate after a task is completed. We can imagine that in some complex cognitive activities, there might be multiple parallel WSIs, each processing different streams of information, but only one or a few can become the #strong[Dominant Workspace Instance (DWSI)], whose content constitutes the core of the current conscious experience @pennartzBrainsRepresentationalPower2015@pennartzWhatNeurorepresentationalismNeural2022.

